  "prompt": "How do I deal with an arrogant teacher?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to deal with an arrogant teacher:\n\n1. Stay professional and respectful\n- Don't become confrontational\n- Maintain a calm and mature attitude\n\n2. Document interactions\n- Keep records of conversations and assignments\n- Note any specific incidents of unfair treatment\n\n3. Communicate effectively\n- Be clear and direct when discussing concerns\n- Use \"I\" statements to express your feelings\n- Focus on specific behaviors, not personal attacks\n\n4. Seek understanding\n- Try to understand why the teacher might be behaving this way\n- Some teachers might be stressed or have personal issues\n\n5. Talk to the teacher privately\n- Request a meeting to discuss your concerns\n- Be specific about what is bothering you\n- Suggest ways to improve communication\n\n6. Involve higher authorities if necessary\n- Speak with a department head, counselor, or principal\n- Provide documented evidence of problematic behavior\n- Maintain a professional tone\n\n7. Focus on your academic performance\n- Do your best work\n- Don't let the teacher's attitude affect your learning\n- Stay motivated and committed to your education\n\n8. Seek support\n- Talk to parents or guardians\n- Discuss the situation with trusted school staff\n- Get advice from peers who might have similar experiences\n\nRemember to remain calm and constructive throughout the process.",
